Subject: Re: [T2] question regarding 72 and 76 brakes

On Sat, 21 Feb 2009, Mike Soultanian wrote:

> Hey Everyone,
> My friend has a 72 bus with warped rotors up front and I guess that's a 
> two-year-only part which is really expensive to replace.  So.... I wanted to 
> find out if it's possible to swap over front disk brake parts from a 76 onto 
> the 72 because I have an extra set of calipers in the garage.  Then he could 
> just purchase new (less expensive) rotors and shoes.

To do this swap you need spindles, calipers, disks, and backing plates.

You might check on the prices for replacement components.  Sometimes it 
isn't as pricy as you think.  Bus Depot shows the 71-72 rotor at only $9 
more than the 73-up rotor.
